Here is a concrete rust snippet:

```rust
fn reverse_string(input: &str) -> String {
    input.chars().rev().collect()
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    #[test]
    fn reverses_ascii() {
        assert_eq!(reverse_string("perci"), "icrep");
    }
}
```
Notes: `chars().rev()` is Unicode-scalar reverse, not grapheme-cluster reverse. For byte-only ASCII you can reverse bytes; for user-visible text, use a grapheme crate when that distinction matters. Compiler/tests beat slogans.

